better or cheaper or both,

507
00:28:58,737 --> 00:29:02,115
and you can do that
if you stick with what
you've got.

508
00:29:02,157 --> 00:29:06,786
There's something
to be said for
ingenuity, no?

509
00:29:06,828 --> 00:29:08,581
Well, sure.
Exactly.

510
00:29:08,622 --> 00:29:11,833
That's what I'm saying.
There's ingenuity in there.

511
00:29:11,875 --> 00:29:14,794
<i>You've been sitting</i>
<i>with this machine</i>
<i>for a few months now.</i>

512
00:29:14,836 --> 00:29:16,672
It's easy to lose sight
of what's great

513
00:29:16,714 --> 00:29:18,965
when it's
right in front of you.
You get used to it.

514
00:29:19,007 --> 00:29:22,678
The computer you two built
is a work of art,

515
00:29:22,720 --> 00:29:24,846
<i>and not only that,</i>
<i>it'll sell.</i>

516
00:29:26,765 --> 00:29:30,852
So you can believe
in your original vision.

517
00:29:30,894 --> 00:29:33,146
You made it all happen.

518
00:29:36,191 --> 00:29:38,527
-<i> ( thunder crashing ) </i>
- Whew, God Alfrighty.

