to build a computer

528
00:30:11,851 --> 00:30:15,063
that'll impress
all the other people
who build computers.

529
00:30:15,105 --> 00:30:16,690
I want to build
something for people

530
00:30:16,732 --> 00:30:19,109
who never thought
they'd want a computer,

531
00:30:19,151 --> 00:30:20,653
who don't know
anything about them.

532
00:30:20,694 --> 00:30:22,279
I want to build
a computer for you.

533
00:30:22,321 --> 00:30:25,115
Hey, now.
I know my way around
a damn computer.

534
00:30:25,157 --> 00:30:27,785
I've been in this business
since before you were
in diapers, kid.

535
00:30:27,826 --> 00:30:29,745
All right.
You know what I mean.

536
00:30:29,787 --> 00:30:33,165
I want to build something
that makes people fall in love.

537
00:30:33,206 --> 00:30:35,167
<i>( faint thunder rumbles )</i>

538
00:30:37,127 --> 00:30:40,130
How'd you fall in love?

539
00:30:43,342 --> 00:30:46,970
Computer Club.

540
00:30:47,012 --> 00:30:50,140
I didn't have
a ton of friends
in junior high.

541
00:30:50,182 --> 00:30:52,309
Oh, I am shocked
by that.

542
00:30:52,351 --> 00:30:54,770
Yeah.

543
00:30:54,812 --> 00:30:59,149
So, yeah, I was hiding out
in a classroom at lunch

544
00:30:59,191 --> 00:31:02,110
and the Computer Club
came in.

545
00:31:02,152 --> 00:31:05,823
I just pretended
I was there on purpose.

546
00:31:05,864 --> 00:31:07,825
Mr. Monroe
taught us BASIC

547
00:31:07,866 --> 00:31:11,286
and it was like
finding water

548
00:31:11,328 --> 00:31:14,289
in the middle
of the desert.

549
00:31:14,331 --> 00:31:17,793
For the first time,
I knew how to talk
to something.

550
00:31:19,252 --> 00:31:21,338
I finally had
the right language.

551
00:31:21,380 --> 00:31:24,883
-<i> ( thunder rumbles ) </i>
- You're talking just fine now.

