to see you shit the bed
on this thing.

563
00:32:00,377 --> 00:32:03,004
Why's that?

564
00:32:03,046 --> 00:32:06,091
'Cause you're the future.

565
00:32:06,132 --> 00:32:08,719
Ain't nothing scarier
than that.

566
00:32:10,345 --> 00:32:12,765
When I was little,
any time there was
a big storm,

567
00:32:12,806 --> 00:32:14,433
my dad would
take us out in it

568
00:32:14,474 --> 00:32:17,352
to show me
there was nothing
to be afraid of.

569
00:32:17,394 --> 00:32:20,105
Then a kid in our
neighborhood got pinned
under a fallen tree

570
00:32:20,146 --> 00:32:22,107
and so he stopped
doing that.

571
00:32:23,983 --> 00:32:27,863
( sighs )
I feel like parenting
used to be different.

572
00:32:27,905 --> 00:32:29,782
<i>( thunder crashing )</i>

573
00:32:29,823 --> 00:32:32,033
My mom used to take me
up to the roof

574
00:32:32,075 --> 00:32:35,203
of our old Victorian
to look at the stars.

575
00:32:35,245 --> 00:32:37,497
That any of us survived
is a miracle.

576
00:32:39,040 --> 00:32:40,876
-<i> ( loud thunderclap ) </i>
- ( screaming )

577
00:32:40,918 --> 00:32:43,378
Hey, hey, it's okay.

578
00:32:43,420 --> 00:32:45,464
You afraid
of the hurricane?

579
00:32:45,505 --> 00:32:47,716
But you've got
hurricane zappers
right here.

580
00:32:47,758 --> 00:32:49,384
You don't know
about hurricane zappers?

581
00:32:49,426 --> 00:32:51,845
Oh, yeah, these.

582
00:32:51,887 --> 00:32:55,223
Just point them
at the storm and it
can't hurt you.

583
00:32:55,265 --> 00:32:57,476
- ( flashlights click )
- Here, I'm telling you
the truth.

584
00:32:57,517 --> 00:33:00,019
- Give it a shot.
- Joanie: It'll work
through the roof?

585
00:33:00,061 --> 00:33:02,898
Oh, yeah.
A bigger storm, you might
need to go outside.

586
00:33:02,940 --> 00:33:05,818
But a little storm
like this, through
the roof should be fine.

587
00:33:07,778 --> 00:33:09,780
- Haley: Let's try it.
- There they go.

588
00:33:11,281 --> 00:33:13,784
<i>( thunder crashing )</i>

